    "description": "<strong>Jigsaw Puzzle Fever</strong> is a single player game that is fun for all the family.  Pick one of the ten starting puzzles to get on your way.<br><br>Each puzzle can be played in one of four difficulty levels:<br>- 48 pieces<br>- 48 pieces with rotated pieces<br>- 108 pieces<br>- 108 pieces with rotated pieces<br><br>The pieces are laid out on the screen - the player simply scrolls through the available pieces<br>and selects a piece.<br><br>Puzzles offer one or more additional features for the player to use:<br><strong>GRID </strong>- Show the grid of the puzzle pieces.<br><strong>EDGES </strong>- Filter the pieces to show only the edge pieces.<br><strong>HELP </strong>– Automatically place one piece in the correct position.<br><strong>PEEK </strong>- Show the full picture.<br><br>Some of the puzzles have forced difficulty settings (e.g. no hints, timer, no peeking).<br><br><strong>Levels</strong><br>Puzzles are grouped into levels. Once all of the initial 10 puzzles have been completed, the<br>next level unlocks. There are 75 puzzles in total.<br><br><strong>Trophies</strong><br>The game will feature trophies which the user can collect by completing various challenges.<br><br><strong>Leaderboards</strong><br>The game will include leaderboards to allow players to post scores with their friends and the rest of the world.",
